
1. Equatorial Guinea is the only country in Africa to have Spanish as an official language.
2. Teodoro Obiang, the current president, is one of the longest-serving presidents in Africa. 
3. The country has the worst record of Human Rights in the world
4. It is the smallest African country to be a member of the United Nations according to the total land area.
5. Equatorial Guinea is the richest country in Africa as its a resource for mineral and oil.
